 [[dark wave]].<ref>https://www.pastemagazine.com/music/charli-xcx/forever/</ref> \n\n==Background==\nOn 9 April 2020, Charli XCX announced that \"Forever\" would be released at 11:30 PM [[Pacific Standard Time|PST]] and premiere on the BBC Radio 1 with Annie Mac podcast. \"Forever\"'s official artwork was done by American artist [[Seth Bogart (artist)]]. Two additional artworks were also released for \"Forever\", one done by French artist Regards Coupables and one done by American singer-songwriter [[Caroline Polachek]].<ref>{{Cite tweet |user=charli_xcx |number=1248287541306036225 |title=\ud83d\udc93 FOREVER DROPS AT 7.30PM BST/11:30AM PST PREMIERING AS HOTTEST RECORD ON @ANNIEMAC ON @BBCR1!!!!! ARTWORK BY @SETHBOGARTOK!!!  2 MORE OFFICIAL ARTWORKS TO COME LATER IN THE DAY \ud83d\udc93 THANK YOU FOR HELPING ME CREATE THE FIRST SONG FROM \"HOW I\u2019M FEELING NOW\" \ud83d\udc93 |date=9 April 2020 |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite tweet |user=charli_xcx |number=1248043315951370240 |title=fyi i am making multiple official artworks for every song I release before the album, maybe even multiple album covers too. the \u201cforever\u201d artwork will be based of the photo we selected together and will be visually interpreted by @SethBogartOK @carolineplz and @regardscoupable \ud83d\udc93 |date=8 April 2020 |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\n\"Forever\" was written by Charli XCX and produced by her, [[A. G. Cook]] and [[BJ Burton]]. It runs for four minutes and three seconds.<ref name= \"Spotify\">{{cite web |title=Forever - Single by Charli XCX on Spotify|url=https://open.spotify.com/album/0yl0sfY3TM3EDLPWghBkfc|website=[[Spotify]]|accessdate= 9 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Release history ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n! scope=\"col\" | Region\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" | Format\n! scope=\"col\" | Label\n! scope=\"col\" | {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Various\n| 9 April 2020\n| {{hlist|[[Music download